---
By: Heraclitus
Source:
  ID: 996c9a12-d13d-4597-a783-506d70cd1736
Verse: 129
Translator: Charles Kahn
Book: Anaximander and the Origins of Greek Cosmology
Publisher: Hackett Publishing
Copyright: 1994
---
Pythagoras, son of Mnesarchus, pursued inquiry further than all other
men and, choosing what he liked from these compositions, claimed for
himself a wisdom of his own - much learning, a bad craft.
